    {
      "type": "action",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/ThreeActions.webp",
      "name": "Absorb Body",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> The corpse orgy begins its turn with a creature @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Grabbed]{Grabbed} and that creature has been reduced to 0 hit points</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The corpse orgy continues its grab and begins to absorb the creature into its mass. If the target creature is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Unconscious]{Unconscious}, they may attempt a @Check[type:fortitude|dc:29] save to resist this absorption.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature becomes @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Doomed]{Doomed 1}, or increases its doomed value by 1 if it was already doomed and the corpse orgy gains 15 temporary hit points.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Doomed]{Doomed 2}. Any creature that dies to this effect is absorbed into the corpse orgy and can only be raised or resurrected if the corpse orgy is slain. If the target creature is not slain by Absorb Body, the corpse orgy extends the duration of its grab until the end of its next turn.</p>"
        },
        "source": {
          "value": ""
        },
